Phase 3: Time-Aware SRS Rating Adapter

Summary:
Implemented a deterministic SRS rating adapter that maps practice submission correctness and timing features to FSRS-style ratings (Again, Hard, Good, Easy).

Key behaviors:
- Base rating derived from submission parts: incorrect/misconceptions → Again, hints/reveals → Hard, clean correct → Good
- Timing applied conservatively as a modifier only when reliable
- Fast + clean + reliable → Easy upgrade
- Slow/very_slow + reliable → Hard downgrade
- Timing never overrides correctness (Again stays Again)

